Introduction

In this lab you are going to use Grub4DOS and Clonezilla to create a recovery partition for Windows 10. Grub4DOS is the DOS based version of GRUB, a multiboot loader. This means you can configure it to start multiple different operating systems. We'll use a live DVD version of CloneZilla as two of the operating systems. One will allow you to create a backup image and one will let you restore a previously created image.

First you'll need to install Windows 10. Then we'll you'll configure Clonezilla and Grub4DOS.

  1. Start VMware workstation and click ’Create a New Virtual Machine’. Select ’Typical (recommended)’ and click next. Select ’I will install the operating system later.’
    2. [help]
  2. Create a virtual machine with 64GB disk, 4GB memory and 2 CPUs and insert the Windows 10 ISO into the DVD drive.
    3. [help]
  3. Select English (United Kingdon) for the Language, Time and currency format. Select United Kingdom for Keyboard or input method.
    4. [help]
  4. Click Install now.
    5. [help]
  5. Enter a KMS key
    6. [help]
  6. Accept the licence terms and click Next
    7. [help]
  7. Click on Custom: Install Windows only (advanced)
    8. [help]
  8. Select Drive 0 and click Next
    9. [help]
  9. You'll have to wait for the installation process to finish.
    10. [help]
  10. Select Use Express Settings.
    11. [help]
  11. Enter a username and password. I used my username and Pa55word as the password. then click Next.
    12. [help]
  12. Select Not now.
    13. [help]
  13. Select Drive 0 and click Next
    14. [help]
  14. Press the Windows Key and type Disk. Select Create and format hard disk partitions.
    15. [help]
  15. Right click on the c: drive and select Shrink Volume.
    16. [help]
  16. For the amount to shrink enter 20000 MB (20 GB) and click Shrink.
    17. [help]
  17. Right click on the unallocated space and select New Simple Volume.
    18. [help]
  18. Click Next.
    19. [help]
  19. Select Drive 0 and click Next
    20. [help]
  20. Allocate the maximum amount of space and click Next.
    21. [help]
  21. Assign the drive to e: and click next.
    22. [help]
  22. Change the name of the volume to Recovery and click Next.
    23. [help]
  23. Click Finish and wait while the disk is formatted. This shouldn't take long.
    24. [help]
  24. From within your newly created VM log into Blackboard go to CO2516, Module Materials, Session 2 and download CloneZillaBackup.zip Extract the contents of CloneZillaBackup to the Recovery drive.
    25. [help]
  25. Right click on e:\clonezilla\installGrub4dos.cmd and select Run as administrator. Press y and then enter.
    26. [help]
  26. Now reboot the VM. You should now see a new boot menu.
    27. [help]
  27. Select 2 Backup Windows. You'll have to be quick as it will default to booting Windows after 10 seconds. After the computer has finished creating an image it will reboot. Alter the desktop in an obvious way, e.g. change the desktop image, or add a folder/file to the desktop. Reboot and select 1 Restore Windows. After the restore has finished the computer will reboot. Check that the changes you made have been remove.
    28. [help]

    Advanced

  28. The boot menu configuration is stored in menu.lst in the e: drive. Alter it so that you can store/restore from multiple image files rather than just one and fix the warning messages.
    29. [help]
